name: Ryan Stutzman
text: Small you pick berry operation, but very reasonable price. No spray herb/pest, eat right from the bush. Super friendly people. My favorite is the Columbus blueberries.

name: Tala McCreless
text: Wonderful family owned business. Lovely place to take out daughter berry picking.

name: Trip Kirby
text: Had a wonderful time with family picking Blueberries

name: Sara Bonds
text: Great people, tasty berries, and beautiful place!

name: Melodie Brier
text: Well mowed walk paths, well spaced bushes, easy picking. I picked 17 pounds of berries in less than 2 hours.  Nice people. Every one was social distancing.  Nice variety of berries to choose from.  You can tell the Zook family are not pushing the berries with a lot of commercial fertilizer because the berries have much more flavor than the ones you get from the grocery store.  Great outdoor activity they welcome families.  Highly reccomend

name: Michaela
text: I loved the experience! The berries were so plump and they taste amazing! I most definitely recommend :)

name: Karin Gilbert
text: Very nice place to pick Blueberries! The owners are very helpful and friendly! Definitely going back

name: Jonathan Hayes
text: Well kept up blueberry farm. Very friendly staff. Would recommend for families looking to get outside.

name: Brian Mullins
text: Very nice, good self pick berry farm.

name: Marjulyn Johnson
text: The owners were very friendly and the blueberries were very sweet!!!

name: Katie Bowers
text: Yummy berries and a sweet family
